</head>

<body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

<div class=WordSection1>

<h1><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>MIPS
Disassembler Project Report<o:p></o:p></span></h1>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #BDC3C7 1.0pt;
mso-border-bottom-alt:solid #BDC3C7 .75pt;padding:0in 0in 4.0pt 0in'>

<h2><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>1.
Project Goal<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

</div>

<p><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>The primary goal of this
project is to develop a simple, and functional MIPS disassembler. The software
reads 32-bit binary machine code instructions from a text file, parses the bit
fields based on MIPS architecture rules, and translates them back into human-readable
MIPS assembly language.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #BDC3C7 1.0pt;
mso-border-bottom-alt:solid #BDC3C7 .75pt;padding:0in 0in 4.0pt 0in'>

<h2><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>2.
Work Distribution <span class=GramE>Across</span> Team Members<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

</div>

<p><span class=GramE><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>the</span></span><span
style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'> workload was distributed across four
primary roles (modules):<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=GramE><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Yaseen
     :</span></b></span><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
     "Times New Roman"'> Responsible for </span><code><span style='font-size:
     10.0pt'>module1_itype.py</span></code><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;
     mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. Focused on decoding immediate
     operations, memory loads/stores (<span class=SpellE><span class=GramE>lw</span></span>,
     <span class=SpellE>sw</span>), and calculating PC-relative targets for
     branch instructions (<span class=SpellE>beq</span>, <span class=SpellE>bne</span>).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=SpellE><span
     class=GramE><b><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
     "Times New Roman"'>Ayham</span></b></span></span><span class=GramE><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     :</span></b></span><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
     "Times New Roman"'> Responsible for </span><code><span style='font-size:
     10.0pt'>module2_rtype.py</span></code><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;
     mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. Focused on extracting <span
     class=SpellE>rs</span>, <span class=SpellE><span class=GramE>rt</span></span>,
     <span class=SpellE>rd</span>, shift amounts, and function codes to decode
     arithmetic, logical, and shift instructions (add, sub, and, <span
     class=SpellE>sll</span>, etc.).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=SpellE><span
     class=GramE><b><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
     "Times New Roman"'>Odai</span></b></span></span><span class=GramE><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     :</span></b></span><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
     "Times New Roman"'> Responsible for </span><code><span style='font-size:
     10.0pt'>module3_jtype_engine.py</span></code><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
     Coordinated the main disassembly loop. Handled J-Type instructions (j, <span
     class=SpellE>jal</span>) and implemented the 2-pass algorithm to calculate
     and assign string labels (e.g., &quot;loop_1&quot;, &quot;func_1&quot;) instead
     of raw addresses.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=GramE><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Ibrahim
     :</span></b></span><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
     "Times New Roman"'> Responsible for </span><code><span style='font-size:
     10.0pt'>module4_qa_formatting.py</span></code><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> and </span><code><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>main.py</span></code><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. Handled
     file reading, input validation (ensuring strictly 32-bit binary strings),
     comment filtering, and final output file writing.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #BDC3C7 1.0pt;
mso-border-bottom-alt:solid #BDC3C7 .75pt;padding:0in 0in 4.0pt 0in'>

<h2><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>3.
Main Functions &amp; Implementations<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

</div>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=SpellE><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>normalize_<span class=GramE>instruction</span></span></b></code></span><span
     class=GramE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>(</span></b></code></span><span
     class=SpellE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>raw_line</span></b></code></span><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>)</span></b></code><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Strips away inline comments and whitespace. Validates that the remaining
     string is exactly 32 bits consisting only of '0's and '1's.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=SpellE><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>decode_<span class=GramE>rtype</span></span></b></code></span><span
     class=GramE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>(</span></b></code></span><span
     class=SpellE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>binary_str</span></b></code></span><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>)</span></b></code><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Slices the 32-bit string into R-type fields (opcode, <span class=SpellE>rs</span>,
     <span class=SpellE>rt</span>, <span class=SpellE>rd</span>, <span
     class=SpellE>shamt</span>, <span class=SpellE>funct</span>). Uses the
     6-bit '<span class=SpellE>funct</span>' code to return the correct
     assembly string (e.g., </span><code><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>add
     $t2, $t0, $t1</span></code><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;
     mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=SpellE><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>decode_<span class=GramE>itype</span></span></b></code></span><span
     class=GramE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>(</span></b></code></span><span
     class=SpellE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>binary_str</span></b></code></span><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>, pc)</span></b></code><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Slices the string into I-type fields (opcode, <span class=SpellE>rs</span>,
     <span class=SpellE>rt</span>, <span class=SpellE>imm</span>). Includes a
     sub-routine to sign-extend the 16-bit immediate using Two's Complement
     logic for signed operations. Returns the formatted assembly string.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=SpellE><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>decode_<span class=GramE>jtype</span></span></b></code></span><span
     class=GramE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>(</span></b></code></span><span
     class=SpellE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>binary_str</span></b></code></span><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>, pc)</span></b></code><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Slices the 26-bit pseudo-absolute address, shifts it left by 2, and
     bitwise-ORs it with the upper 4 bits of the PC to find the true jump
     target.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>analyze_<span class=GramE>pass1(</span><span
     class=SpellE>binary_instructions</span>, <span class=SpellE>base_address</span>)</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     The first step of the disassembly engine. Iterates over all instructions
     to calculate targets for any branch or jump. If a target points to a valid
     address inside the program, it assigns a dictionary key with a generated
     label (</span><span class=SpellE><code><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>loop_X</span></code></span><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     or </span><span class=SpellE><code><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>func_X</span></code></span><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'><span class=GramE><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>disassemble(</span></b></code></span><span
     class=SpellE><code><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>binary_instructions</span></b></code></span><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>)</span></b></code><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     The core coordinator. First, it calls </span><code><span style='font-size:
     10.0pt'>analyze_pass1</span></code><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;
     mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. Then, it iterates through the
     instructions a second time, dispatching them to the R, I, or J decoders.
     If an instruction references an internal address, it replaces the raw hex
     address with the previously generated label.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #BDC3C7 1.0pt;
mso-border-bottom-alt:solid #BDC3C7 .75pt;padding:0in 0in 4.0pt 0in'>

<h2><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>4.
Test Cases<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

</div>

<p><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>We created a comprehensive </span><code><span
style='font-size:10.0pt'>tests/</span></code><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif'>
directory covering all grading criteria:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>arithmetic_sample1.txt</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Tests R-type and I-type arithmetic (Signed vs Unsigned).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>if_sample1.txt</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Tests branch decoding and comparisons (<span class=SpellE>slt</span>, <span
     class=SpellE>beq</span>, <span class=SpellE>bne</span>).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>memory_sample1.txt</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Tests memory offsets and loading/storing (<span class=SpellE><span
     class=GramE>lw</span></span>, <span class=SpellE>sw</span>, <span
     class=SpellE>lbu</span>, <span class=SpellE>lui</span>).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>jump_sample1.txt</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Tests absolute jumps and jump registers (j, <span class=SpellE>jal</span>,
     <span class=SpellE><span class=GramE>jr</span></span>).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>function_sample1.txt</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Tests call/return procedure flow.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>arrays_sample1.txt</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Tests iterating memory pointers over an array loop.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><code><b><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>loops_sample1.txt</span></b></code><b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:</span></b><span
     style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
     Tests loop reconstruction.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<div style='mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid #BDC3C7 1.0pt;
mso-border-bottom-alt:solid #BDC3C7 .75pt;padding:0in 0in 4.0pt 0in'>

<h2><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>5.
Challenges Faced<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

</div>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l1 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Immediate
     Sign Extension:</span></b><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;
     mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> Python handles binary numbers
     at an arbitrary width, making standard bitwise operations for negative
     numbers difficult. We had to implement a custom algorithm to check if the
     16th bit was high (0x8000), and if so, subtract 65536 to emulate native
     hardware signed 2's complement.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l1 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Label
     Resolution:</span></b><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;
     mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> Simply outputting jump targets
     as &quot;0x00400014&quot; is not true human-readable assembly. The
     challenge was tracking forward-referencing targets before the engine had
     reached those addresses. We solved this by implementing a 2-pass
     architecture, ensuring all labels were discovered before any string
     formatting occurred.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-bottom:6.0pt;
     mso-list:l1 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'><b><span style='font-family:
     "Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Branch
     Addressing:</span></b><span style='font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;
     mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> Accurately replicating the
     MIPS PC-relative branch formula (PC + 4 + (offset &lt;&lt; 2)) required
     careful tracking of the simulated program counter during both passes.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

</div>

</body>

</html>
